Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Dermaseptin-DI4 (Dermaseptin DI4, DRS-DI4, dermadistinctin Q1, DDQ1; DD Q1; UCLL1; natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals)
Sequence Information.Source: the Brazilian frog Phyllomedusa distincta, South America

Literature Information.Literature: Activity: Active against E. faecalis (MIC 22 uM), P. aeruginosa (MIC 5.4 uM), E. coli (MIC 1.3 uM), S. aureus (MIC 2.7 uM).Toxicity: Hemolysis >36 uM. Also provided by Erik Martin. Updated 6/2015; 7/2021
Literature Information.Author: Batista CV, da Silva LR, Sebben A, Scaloni A, Ferrara L, Paiva GR, Olamendi-Portugal T, Possani LD, Bloch C Jr1999
Literature Information.Title: Antimicrobial peptides from the Brazilian frog Phyllomedusa distincta.
